{How would you continue?} 20. d5 $1 {Of course. Once Black has weakened his
control over d5, this breakthrough is powerful.} exd5 21. Nxd5 {[%cal Gd3f5]}
h6 (21... Qxd5 $2 {runs into} 22. Bxg6 $1 $18) 22. Ne7+ $1 {The only way of
keeping the initiative alive.} Nxe7 23. Nxf7 $1 {Same comment.} Kxf7 (23...
Rxf7 24. Bxg6 Nxg6 25. Rxd8+ $18 {is even worse for Black.}) 24. Rxe7+ $1 {
Forcing Black to expose his queen.} Qxe7 25. Bxg6+ $1 Kxg6 26. Qxe7 $16 {
The material balance is roughly even, and the queen is very strong, giving the
black king exposure and Black's lack of coordination.} *

