{What was wrong with Black's king lift?} 20. Bc4 $1 {Black has delayed his
minor pieces' regrouping too much and suddenly this move creates very serious
threats.} (20. Rxe6 $2 {was played in Rozentalis,E (2570)-Gheorghiu,F (2495)
Suhr 1991 (0-1, 41). This irresistible combination does not yield White an
advantage. You will explain it later.}) 20... Ne7 (20... h6 {runs into} 21.
Nxf7 Rxf7 22. Bxe6 $16 Rf8 $2 23. d5 Ne7 24. d6 $18) 21. Bxe6 h6 22. Nxf7 Rxf7
23. d5 $16 {White can take on c8 or f7 anytime, restoring the approximate
material equality and keeping strong pressure.} *

