{Did Black just lose a pawn?} 20... h6 $1 {Not really! This move forces White
to sacrifice a knight under unclear circumstances.} 21. Nxf7 Rxf7 22. d5 Ne7 {
In the line recommended on move 20, White would have a bishop on e6 instead of
a rook. This makes a big (material) difference. The position is just unclear
now.} ({The game continued:} 22... Ne7 23. d6 Ned5 (23... Neg8 24. Qd4 (24. Qg3
Rc5 25. Qxg6+ Kf8 $15) 24... Qd7 25. Re2 Qg4 26. Qxg4 Nxg4 27. Bc4 Rxc4 28. d7
Rf8 29. Re8 Rxf2 30. d8=Q Rxg2+ 31. Kf1 Nxh2+ 32. Ke1 Nf3+ 33. Kf1 $11) (23...
g5 24. Qg3 Ng6 $13) 24. Qg3 g5 25. h4 (25. Ne2 $5 Bc6 {[%cal Gc6d7]}) 25... Nf4
26. Ree1 N6h5 27. Qg4 Nf6 (27... Bxg2 $19) (27... Rc5 $19) 28. Qf5 Rc5 29. Re5
Bc8 30. Rxc5 Bxf5 31. Rxf5 Qxd6 32. hxg5 hxg5 33. Rxg5+ Kh6 34. Rg3 Rg7 35. Bf1
Qc6 36. Rxg7 Kxg7 37. g3 Ne6 38. Bg2 Qc5 39. Re1 Nd4 40. Re3 Ng4 41. Re4 Nf3+ {
0-1 Rozentalis,E (2570) -Gheorghiu,F (2495) Suhr 1991}) *

