{How should White continue his attack?} 23. Nxh6+ $1 {This sacrifice wins, but
only in combination with the next move.} (23. d5 $1 {is as strong as the main
line move. Without disclosing too much, I would just mention that the defence}
Bb5 {runs into} 24. dxe6 Bxd3 25. exf7+ Kh8 26. Rxd3 $18) 23... Kh8 {The best
try. Black hopes to gain some material under bearable circumstances.} (23...
gxh6 $2 24. Qg4+ Kh8 25. Bxh6 Bf8 26. Bf4 {yields White a decisive attack.
Black's queen is still on b8!} f5 27. Qg3 Bd6 28. Bxe6 Ba4 29. Bxd6 Qxd6 30.
Qxd6 Rxd6 31. Bxc8 $18) 24. d5 $1 {Only this move wins. White needs to clear
space for the retreat of his knight, or else to weaken Black's kingside.} (24.
Ng4 Bb5 {is unclear.}) 24... gxh6 (24... exd5 {allows} 25. Nf5 {and if} Bb5 26.
Qg4 $18) 25. dxe6 $18 {with a decisive attack.} *

