{Black seems to be well regrouped for defensive purposes. Is that right?} 34.
e4 $1 {Bobo para Grigor d4 Semihanging; Stohl,I No, it is not! The pin along
the fifth rank costs Black dearly.} Rd7 $2 {AFter this move, Black does not
have chances to save the game.} (34... fxe4+ $2 {is also bad.} 35. Rxe4+ Kd6
36. Rxe7 Kxe7 37. Rxa7+ Ke6 38. Rxh7 $18) (34... Ke6 $1 {was the only
reasonable defence.} 35. exd5+ cxd5 36. Raxd5 Ra6 37. a4 Rc7 $16 {Black can
still hope.}) 35. exd5 cxd5 36. Rda4 Rbb7 ({The game went} 36... h5 37. Rxa7
Rxa7 38. Rxa7 {and White won.} (38. f4+ $5 Ke6 39. Rxa7 $18) 38... f4 39. Re7+
Kf6 40. Re2 g5 41. Kd4 {Bobo para Grigor d4 Semihanging; Stohl,I} Rc6 42. Kxd5
Rc3 43. Re6+ Kf5 44. Re5+ Kg6 45. gxf4 gxf4 46. Ke4 Rc2 47. f3 Rh2 48. Kxf4
Rxh3 49. Re6+ Kf7 50. Rb6 Ke7 51. a4 Kd7 52. a5 Kc7 53. b4 Rh1 54. Kg5 h4 55.
Rh6 h3 56. f4 h2 57. Kf5 Rb1 58. Rxh2 Rxb4 59. Rc2+ {1-0 Stohl,I (2530)
-Ftacnik,L (2605) Vinkovci 1995}) 37. Ra6 $1 {[%cal Gf2f4] The threat f2-f4
mate forces Black to give up a pawn.} f4 (37... d4 38. f4+ Kd5 39. R4a5+ {
mates next.}) 38. Rxf4 $18 *

