{Black's last move was the natural 14...Re8 and position looks solid. White
found a way to prove it was not. Your move.} 15. Rxe6 $3 {Bob para Grigor d4
Semihanging A winning sacrifice.} (15. Bb1 {is inoffesnive due to} Ng6 {
, revealing the hidden idea behind ...Re8. White does not have Rxe6 now.})
15... fxe6 (15... Nxd4 {was an important alternative. You will deal with it in
the next test.}) 16. Bxe6+ Kf8 (16... Kh8 $4 {is worse, as you will have the
occasion to prove. Why did Black's king avoid the apparently safe corner?} 17.
Ng5 $18 {This wins instantly.} hxg5 18. Qh3#) 17. Nh4 {Threatening 18.Qf5+ Nf5
19.Ng6#} (17. Qh7 {was another strong attacking continuation.} Nd5 (17... Ng6
18. Qxg6 Qf6 19. Qxf6+ gxf6 20. Bxh6+ Ke7 21. Re1 Na5 22. Nh4) 18. Qg8+ Ke7 19.
Qf7+ Kd6 20. Bxd5 $18) (17. Bxh6 $5 {wins, too.}) 17... Ne5 {The best chance.}
18. Qh7 $1 {All other moves lose, but this wins.} N7c6 (18... Nf7 19. Bxh6 $3 {
The shortest win, indicated by Tal, as many other lines examined here.} Nxh6
20. Qh8+ Nhg8 21. Qxg8+ $3 Nxg8 22. Ng6#) (18... N7g6 19. Qg8+ (19. Qxg6 $2
Qxh4 $1 20. dxe5 Rxe6 21. Qxe6 Qe4 $1 $19)) (18... Nd5 19. Qg8+ Ke7 20. Nf5+
Kf6 21. dxe5+ Kxe5 22. f4+ Ke4 (22... Nxf4 23. Bxf4+ Kxf4 24. Rf1+ $18) 23.
Nd6+ {!} Qxd6 24. Qh7+ $18) (18... N5g6 19. Qg8+ $18) 19. Qg8+ (19. Bxh6 $5
Rxe6 20. Bxg7+ Ke8 21. dxe5 $18) 19... Ke7 20. Nf5+ Kf6 21. dxe5+ Nxe5 (21...
Kxe5 22. f4+ Ke4 23. Nd6+ Qxd6 24. Qh7+ $18 {Tal}) 22. Qxg7+ Kxe6 23. Nd4+ Kd6
24. Bf4 $18 {Black cannot save his pinned knight, meaning that White will have
two paws for the exchange and a continuing attack.} ({Tal rejected} 24. Qxb7 {
because of} Qd7 25. Qa6 $1 $18 {Marin} (25. Qe4 $2 Nf3+ $1 $19) (25. Qxd7+ Kxd7
26. Bxh6 $13 {Tal, +/- Marin})) (24. Bf4 $1 $18 {The game continued} Bd5 25.
Re1 Kc5 26. Rxe5 Rxe5 27. Qxe5 Qd7 28. Nc2 Re8 29. Qd4+ Kc6 30. c4 Be6 31. Qe4+
Kc5 32. h3 Bf5 33. Be3+ Kd6 34. Qf4+ {1-0 Tal,M-Myagmarsuren,L Nice 1974}) *

