{White's previous move was 17.b4. Is that a sound pawn sacrifice?} 17... cxb4
$1 {With some calculating, Black would have understood that this simply wins a
pawn.} (17... Qxb4 $2 {loses material.} 18. Rb1 $18) (17... c4 $6 {is an
obvious positional concession.} 18. Nd4 Qe8 19. Nb6 Ra7 20. Nf5 $16) (17...
Rac8 $2 {This "cooperative" move yields White a clear advantage.} 18. bxc5 Bxc5
19. Bxf6 gxf6 20. Nxc5 Qxc5 21. Qf5 $16 {Marshall,F-Tarrasch,S Nuremberg 1905 
(1-0, 39)}) (17... d4 {is a sound move, answering an attack on the wing with a
counter blow in the centre. However, it does not "punish" the last movie.} 18.
bxc5 (18. exd4 Be4 19. Qb3 c4 $19) (18. Nxc5 Bxf3 19. gxf3 dxe3 20. fxe3 Qxb4
$15) 18... Be4 (18... dxe3 19. fxe3 Be4 $11) 19. Qb3 dxe3 20. fxe3 Bxc5 $11 21.
Qxb5 $2 Bxe3+ 22. Kh1 axb5 $19) 18. Nd4 Rac8 $1 {An essential intermediate
move.} ({Both players might have considered only} 18... Qe8 19. Nb6 Ra7 20. Nf5
$14 {with overwhelming compensation for the pawn. Black has to worry about
Nxg7 followed by Qf5 already.}) 19. Qb3 (19. Nxb5 Rxc2 20. Nd4 Rxa2 $19) 19...
Qe8 $17 {White does not have compensation for the pawn.} *

