{Black has just taken on c4. What should White do about it?} 19. Nxf7 $1 {
Unblocking the d4-pawn should have had lethal consequences for Black. This
sacrifice takes full advantage of White's superior coordination.} (19. Nxc6 $5
{During the previous phase I tried finding ways of sacrificing on f7 or e6
after Nf3-g5, but when everything was ready for it I answered almost
automatically. This is not a bad movie, but it does not win.} Bxc6 20. bxc4 $14
{One of the reasons I did not look deeper was that White's position remains
very pleasant after the game continuation anyway.} Bb7 $6 {This is the subject
of the next test.} (20... Rd6 $5 {[%cal Gd6f6]} 21. Bc2 $5 Red8 22. Bb3 $14 {
[%cal Gd4d5]})) (19. bxc4 $2 {is simply bad.} Nxe5 20. dxe5 Ne4 $15) 19... Kxf7
20. d5 {All I would have needed would have been the bell ringing "tactics" as
the idea is quite logical. White attacks with all his pieces.} Kg8 {is the
only move avoiding instant loss, but Black's position remains horrible after} (
20... Nxd5 21. Qh5+ Ke7 22. Nxd5+ exd5 23. Rxd5 $18) (20... Rxd5 21. Bxf6 Rxd1+
22. Rxd1 Kxf6 23. Rd7 Re7 24. Qf3+) (20... exd5 21. Bxf6 $18) 21. dxc6 Bxc6 22.
Qxc4 $16 {/+-} *

